aracter.Hegarty and Lambe are the only two survivors of the Irish women's four from Tokyo, as Fiona Murtagh and Aifric Keogh are now in the Irish women's pair.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9695785990972475, \"rank\": 0.0211213845715724, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"score\": 0.6569245140156686, \"rank\": 0.5217947525896499, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\"}, {\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\", \"score\": 0.999998793390478, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fiona Murtagh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fiona_Murtagh\"}, {\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aifric Keogh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aifric_Keogh\"}, {\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9695785990972475, \"rank\": 0.0211213845715724, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Skibbereen rower Hegarty\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire 2023 international season\